          'X-Title': 'Student-AI-Hackathon-App'

  const { notes } = req.body;

  try {
    const response = await axios.post(
      'https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions',
      {
        model: 'anthropic/claude-3-sonnet-20240229',
        messages: [
          {
            role: 'user',

Notes:
${notes}

Format:

   a) Option 1

   d) Option 4
Answer: b

Only provide the quiz text.`
          }

          'Content-Type': 'application/json',
          'HTTP-Referer': 'http://localhost:3000',

    );

    if (!quiz.length) {

    console.error('OpenRouter API error:', error?.response?.data || error.message);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to generate quiz.' });
  }

// Function to parse raw quiz text into structured JSON
const parseQuiz = (raw) => {
  const lines = raw.split("\n").map(line => line.trim()).filter(Boolean);
  const parsedQuiz = [];
  let currentQuestion = null;

  lines.forEach(line => {
    if (/^\d+\./.test(line)) {
      if (currentQuestion) parsedQuiz.push(currentQuestion);
      currentQuestion = {
        question: line.replace(/^\d+\.\s*/, ""),
        options: [],
        correctIndex: null
      };
    } else if (/^[a-dA-D]\)/.test(line)) {
      currentQuestion?.options.push(line.replace(/^[a-dA-D]\)\s*/, ""));
    } else if (/^Answer:/i.test(line)) {
      const match = line.match(/^Answer:\s*([a-dA-D])/i);
      if (match && currentQuestion) {
        currentQuestion.correctIndex = match[1].toLowerCase().charCodeAt(0) - 97;
      }
    }
  });

  if (currentQuestion) parsedQuiz.push(currentQuestion);
  return parsedQuiz;
};

const PORT = 4000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`✅ Backend running on http://localhost:${PORT}`);
});

import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';

export default function QuizGenerator() {
  const [notes, setNotes] = useState('');
  const navigate = useNavigate();

  const generateQuiz = async () => {
    try {
      const res = await fetch('/api/generate-quiz', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ notes }),
      });

      const data = await res.json();

      if (data.error) {
        alert('Error generating quiz: ' + data.error);
        return;
      }

      localStorage.setItem('quizRaw', data.quizRaw);
      navigate('/quiz');
    } catch (e) {
      alert('Network error: ' + e.message);
    }
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Enter Notes to Generate Quiz</h2>
      <textarea
        value={notes}
        onChange={(e) => setNotes(e.target.value)}
        rows={10}
        cols={50}
      />
      <br />
      <button onClick={generateQuiz} disabled={!notes.trim()}>
        Generate Quiz
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}

2. QuizPage.js (Your updated quiz page, parsing quizRaw from localStorage)

jsx
import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";
import "./QuizPage.css";

export default function QuizPage() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();
  const [quizRaw, setQuizRaw] = useState("");
  const [quiz, setQuiz] = useState([]);
  const [userAnswers, setUserAnswers] = useState({});
  const [score, setScore] = useState(0);
  const [quizFinished, setQuizFinished] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem("quizRaw");
    if (!raw) {
      alert("⚠️ No quiz found. Redirecting to assistant page.");
      navigate("/assistant");
      return;
    }
    setQuizRaw(raw);
    parseQuiz(raw);
  }, [navigate]);

  const parseQuiz = (raw) => {
    const lines = raw
      .split("\n")
      .map((line) => line.trim())
      .filter(Boolean);

    const parsed = [];
    let currentQuestion = null;

    lines.forEach((line) => {
      if (/^\d+\./.test(line)) {
        if (currentQuestion) parsed.push(currentQuestion);
        currentQuestion = {
          question: line.replace(/^\d+\.\s*/, ""),
          options: [],
          correctIndex: null,
        };
      } else if (/^[a-dA-D]\)/.test(line)) {
        currentQuestion?.options.push(line.replace(/^[a-dA-D]\)\s*/, ""));
      } else if (/^Answer:/i.test(line)) {
        const match = line.match(/^Answer:\s*([a-dA-D])/i);
        if (match && currentQuestion) {
          const index = match[1].toLowerCase().charCodeAt(0) - 97;
          currentQuestion.correctIndex = index;
        }
      }
    });

    if (currentQuestion) parsed.push(currentQuestion);

    if (parsed.length === 0) {
      alert("⚠️ Unable to parse quiz. Check backend response format.");
    }

    setQuiz(parsed);
  };

  const handleAnswer = (qIndex, oIndex) => {
    if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined || quizFinished) return;

    const isCorrect = quiz[qIndex].correctIndex === oIndex;

    setUserAnswers((prev) => {
      const newAnswers = { ...prev, [qIndex]: oIndex };
      if (Object.keys(newAnswers).length === quiz.length) {
        setQuizFinished(true);
      }
      return newAnswers;
    });

    if (isCorrect) {
      setScore((prev) => prev + 1);
    }
  };

  const restart = () => {
    setUserAnswers({});
    setScore(0);
    setQuizFinished(false);
  };

  const goBack = () => {
    navigate("/assistant");
  };

  return (
    <div className="quiz-page">
      <h1>🧠 Quiz Game</h1>
      <p>
        Score: {score} / {quiz.length}
      </p>

      {quiz.map((q, qIndex) => (
        <div className="quiz-question" key={qIndex}>
          <p>
            <strong>
              Q{qIndex + 1}. {q.question}
            </strong>
          </p>
          <ul className="options-list">
            {q.options.map((opt, oIndex) => {
              const selected = userAnswers[qIndex] === oIndex;
              const correct = q.correctIndex === oIndex;
              let className = "";

              if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined) {
                if (selected && correct) className = "correct";
                else if (selected && !correct) className = "wrong";
                else if (!selected && correct) className = "correct";
              }

              return (
                <li
                  key={oIndex}
                  className={className}
                  onClick={() => handleAnswer(qIndex, oIndex)}
                  style={{

jsx
import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { useNavigate, useLocation } from "react-router-dom";
import "./QuizPage.css";

export default function QuizPage() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();
  const location = useLocation();
  const quizRaw = location.state?.quizRaw || "";

  const [quiz, setQuiz] = useState([]);
  const [userAnswers, setUserAnswers] = useState({});
  const [score, setScore] = useState(0);
  const [quizFinished, setQuizFinished] = useState(false);
  const [showPopup, setShowPopup] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!quizRaw) {
      navigate("/assistant");
      return;
    }
    parseQuiz(quizRaw);
  }, [quizRaw, navigate]);

  const parseQuiz = (raw) => {
    const lines = raw
      .split("\n")
      .map((line) => line.trim())
      .filter(Boolean);

    const parsed = [];
    let currentQuestion = null;

    lines.forEach((line) => {
      if (/^\d+\./.test(line)) {
        if (currentQuestion) parsed.push(currentQuestion);
        currentQuestion = {
          question: line.replace(/^\d+\.\s*/, ""),
          options: [],
          correctIndex: null,
        };
      } else if (/^[a-dA-D]\)/.test(line)) {
        currentQuestion?.options.push(line.replace(/^[a-dA-D]\)\s*/, ""));
      } else if (/^Answer:/i.test(line)) {
        const match = line.match(/^Answer:\s*([a-dA-D])/);
        if (match) {
          const index = match[1].toLowerCase().charCodeAt(0) - 97;
          currentQuestion.correctIndex = index;
        }
      }
    });

    if (currentQuestion) parsed.push(currentQuestion);
    setQuiz(parsed);
  };

  const handleAnswer = (qIndex, oIndex) => {
    if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined || quizFinished) return;

    const isCorrect = quiz[qIndex].correctIndex === oIndex;
    setUserAnswers((prev) => ({ ...prev, [qIndex]: oIndex }));
    if (isCorrect) setScore((prev) => prev + 1);

    if (Object.keys(userAnswers).length + 1 === quiz.length) {
      setQuizFinished(true);
      setShowPopup(true);
    }
  };

  const restart = () => {
    setUserAnswers({});
    setScore(0);
    setQuizFinished(false);
    setShowPopup(false);
  };

  const goBack = () => {
    navigate("/assistant");
  };

  return (
    <div className="quiz-page">
      <h1>🧠 Quiz Time</h1>
      <p>
        Score: {score} / {quiz.length}
      </p>

      {quiz.map((q, qIndex) => (
        <div className="quiz-question" key={qIndex}>
          <p>
            <strong>
              Q{qIndex + 1}. {q.question}
            </strong>
          </p>
          <ul className="options-list">
            {q.options.map((opt, oIndex) => {
              const selected = userAnswers[qIndex] === oIndex;
              const correct = q.correctIndex === oIndex;
              let className = "";

              if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined) {
                if (selected && correct) className = "correct";
                else if (selected) className = "wrong";
                else if (correct) className = "correct";
              }

              return (
                <li
                  key={oIndex}
                  className={className}
                  onClick={() => handleAnswer(qIndex, oIndex)}
                  style={{ cursor: userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined ? "default" : "pointer" }}
                >
                  {opt}
                </li>
              );
            })}
          </ul>

          {userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined && (
            <p className="result-msg">
              {userAnswers[qIndex] === q.correctIndex ? (
                "✅ Correct!"
              ) : (
                <span>
                  ❌ Wrong. Correct: <strong>{q.options[q.correctIndex]}</strong>
                </span>
              )}
            </p>
          )}
        </div>
      ))}

      <div className="quiz-actions">
        {quizFinished && <button onClick={restart}>🔁 Restart</button>}
        <button onClick={goBack}>🏠 Back to Summary</button>
      </div>

      {showPopup && (
        <div className="score-popup">
          <div className="popup-content">
            <h2>🎉 Quiz Completed!</h2>
            <p>
              Your score is {score} out of {quiz.length}
            </p>
            <button onClick={() => setShowPopup(false)}>Close</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

// Quiz generation endpoint
app.post('/api/generate-quiz', async (req, res) => {
  const { notes } = req.body;

  try {
    const response = await axios.post(
      'https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions',
      {
        model: 'anthropic/claude-3-sonnet-20240229',

          {

Notes:
${notes}

Format:
1. Sample question?
   a) Option 1
   b) Option 2
   c) Option 3
   d) Option 4
Answer: b

Only provide the quiz text.`
          }
        ],
        max_tokens: 800
      },
      {
        headers: {
          Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENROUTER_API_KEY}`, // <-- Correct template literal
          'Content-Type': 'application/json',
          'HTTP-Referer': 'http://localhost:3000',
          'X-Title': 'Student-AI-Hackathon-App'
        }
      }
    );

    const rawQuiz = response.data.choices[0].message.content;
    const quiz = parseQuiz(rawQuiz);

    res.json({ quizRaw: rawQuiz, quiz });

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('OpenRouter API error:', error?.response?.data || error.message);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to generate quiz.' });
  }
});

// Function to parse raw quiz text into a structured object
const parseQuiz = (raw) => {
  const lines = raw.split("\n").map(line => line.trim()).filter(Boolean);
  const parsedQuiz = [];
  let currentQuestion = null;

  lines.forEach(line => {
    if (/^\d+\./.test(line)) {
      if (currentQuestion) parsedQuiz.push(currentQuestion);
      currentQuestion = {
        question: line.replace(/^\d+\.\s*/, ""),
        options: [],
        correctIndex: null
      };
    } else if (/^[a-dA-D]\)/.test(line)) {
      currentQuestion?.options.push(line.replace(/^[a-dA-D]\)\s*/, ""));
    } else if (/^Answer:/i.test(line)) {
      const match = line.match(/^Answer:\s*([a-dA-D])/i);
      if (match && currentQuestion) {
        currentQuestion.correctIndex = match[1].toLowerCase().charCodeAt(0) - 97;
      }
    }
  });

  if (currentQuestion) parsedQuiz.push(currentQuestion);
  return parsedQuiz;
};

const PORT = 4000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`✅ Backend running on http://localhost:${PORT}`);
});

js
import axios from 'axios';
import express from 'express';
import dotenv from 'dotenv';
import cors from 'cors';

dotenv.config();

const app = express();
app.use(cors()); // Allows all origins, good for localhost dev
app.use(express.json());

// Summarize endpoint
app.post('/api/summarize', async (req, res) => {
  const { notes } = req.body;

  try {
    const response = await axios.post(
      'https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions',
      {
        model: 'anthropic/claude-3-sonnet-20240229',
        messages: [
          {
            role: 'user',
            content: `Short Summary:\n${notes}`,
          },
        ],
        max_tokens: 500,
      },
      {
        headers: {
          Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENROUTER_API_KEY}`,
          'Content-Type': 'application/json',
          'HTTP-Referer': 'http://localhost:3000',
          'X-Title': 'Student-AI-Hackathon-App',
        },
      }
    );

    const summary = response.data.choices[0].message.content;
    res.json({ summary });
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('OpenRouter API error:', error?.response?.data || error.message);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to generate summary.' });
  }
});

// Quiz generation endpoint
app.post('/api/generate-quiz', async (req, res) => {
  const { notes } = req.body;

  try {
    const response = await axios.post(
      'https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions',
      {
        model: 'anthropic/claude-3-sonnet-20240229',
        messages: [
          {
            role: 'user',
            content: `Generate a quiz based on the following notes. Provide questions with multiple-choice options. Include the correct answer at the end of each question using the format: "Answer: a".

Notes:
${notes}

Format:
1. Sample question?
   a) Option 1
   b) Option 2
   c) Option 3
   d) Option 4
Answer: b

Only provide the quiz text.`,
          },
        ],
        max_tokens: 800,
      },
      {
        headers: {
          Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENROUTER_API_KEY}`,
          'Content-Type': 'application/json',
          'HTTP-Referer': 'http://localhost:3000',
          'X-Title': 'Student-AI-Hackathon-App',
        },
      }
    );

    const rawQuiz = response.data.choices[0].message.content;
    res.json({ quizRaw: rawQuiz }); // send raw text, parsing happens frontend
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('OpenRouter API error:', error?.response?.data || error.message);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to generate quiz.' });
  }
});

const PORT = 4000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`✅ Backend running on http://localhost:${PORT}`);

1. App.js (Summarizer + Quiz generator UI)

jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import "./App.css";
import { ToastContainer, toast } from "react-toastify";
import "react-toastify/dist/ReactToastify.css";
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";

function App() {
  const [notes, setNotes] = useState("");
  const [summary, setSummary] = useState("");
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const navigate = useNavigate();

  useEffect(() => {
    const savedSummary = localStorage.getItem("summary");
    if (savedSummary) setSummary(savedSummary);
  }, []);

  useEffect(() => {
    summary
      ? localStorage.setItem("summary", summary)
      : localStorage.removeItem("summary");
  }, [summary]);

  const handleSummarize = async () => {
    if (!notes.trim()) {
      toast.error("⚠ Please enter some notes first!");
      return;
    }

    try {
      setLoading(true);
      toast.info("⏳ Generating summary...");

      const response = await fetch("http://localhost:4000/api/summarize", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({ notes }),
      });

      const data = await response.json();
      setLoading(false);

      if (data.summary) {
        setSummary(data.summary);
        toast.success("✅ Summary generated!");
      } else {
        toast.error("❌ Failed to get summary.");
      }
    } catch (err) {
      console.error(err);
      setLoading(false);
      toast.error("⚠ Backend error.");
    }
  };

  const handleQuiz = async () => {
    if (!notes.trim()) {
      toast.error("⚠ Please enter some notes first!");
      return;
    }

    try {
      setLoading(true);
      toast.info("⏳ Generating quiz...");

      const response = await fetch("http://localhost:4000/api/generate-quiz", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({ notes }),
      });

      const data = await response.json();
      setLoading(false);

      if (data.quizRaw) {
        localStorage.setItem("quizRaw", data.quizRaw);
        toast.success("✅ Quiz generated!");
        navigate("/quiz");
      } else {
        toast.error("❌ Failed to get quiz.");
      }
    } catch (err) {
      console.error(err);
      setLoading(false);
      toast.error("⚠ Backend error.");
    }
  };

  const handleClear = () => {
    setNotes("");
    setSummary("");
    localStorage.removeItem("summary");
    localStorage.removeItem("quizRaw");
    window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: "smooth" });
    toast.success("✅ Reset complete!");
  };

  return (
    <div className="App">
      <div className="content-wrapper">
        <h1>📚 SmartBuddy</h1>

        <textarea
          rows="10"
          placeholder="Paste your notes here..."
          value={notes}
          onChange={(e) => setNotes(e.target.value)}
        />

        <div className="button-group">
          <button onClick={handleSummarize} disabled={loading}>
            {loading ? "Summarizing..." : "Summarize"}
          </button>
          <button onClick={handleQuiz} disabled={loading}>
            {loading ? "Generating Quiz..." : "Generate Quiz"}
          </button>
          <button onClick={handleClear}>Clear All</button>
        </div>

        {summary && (
          <div className="section-box">
            <h2>📄 Summary</h2>
            <p>{summary}</p>
          </div>
        )}
      </div>

      <ToastContainer position="top-right" autoClose={2000} />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;

2. QuizPage.js (Quiz interface & logic)

jsx
import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";
import "./QuizPage.css";

export default function QuizPage() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();
  const [quiz, setQuiz] = useState([]);
  const [userAnswers, setUserAnswers] = useState({});
  const [score, setScore] = useState(0);
  const [quizFinished, setQuizFinished] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem("quizRaw");
    if (!raw) {
      navigate("/assistant");
      return;
    }
    parseQuiz(raw);
  }, [navigate]);

  const parseQuiz = (raw) => {
    const lines = raw
      .split("\n")
      .map((line) => line.trim())
      .filter(Boolean);

    const parsed = [];
    let currentQuestion = null;

    lines.forEach((line) => {
      if (/^\d+\./.test(line)) {
        if (currentQuestion) parsed.push(currentQuestion);
        currentQuestion = {
          question: line.replace(/^\d+\.\s*/, ""),
          options: [],
          correctIndex: null,
        };
      } else if (/^[a-dA-D]\)/.test(line)) {
        currentQuestion?.options.push(line.replace(/^[a-dA-D]\)\s*/, ""));
      } else if (/^Answer:/i.test(line)) {
        const match = line.match(/^Answer:\s*([a-dA-D])/);
        if (match) {
          currentQuestion.correctIndex = match[1].toLowerCase().charCodeAt(0) - 97;
        }
      }
    });

    if (currentQuestion) parsed.push(currentQuestion);
    setQuiz(parsed);
  };

  const handleAnswer = (qIndex, oIndex) => {
    if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined || quizFinished) return;

    const isCorrect = quiz[qIndex].correctIndex === oIndex;
    setUserAnswers((prev) => ({ ...prev, [qIndex]: oIndex }));
    if (isCorrect) setScore((prev) => prev + 1);

    if (Object.keys(userAnswers).length + 1 === quiz.length) {
      setQuizFinished(true);
    }
  };

  const restart = () => {
    setUserAnswers({});
    setScore(0);
    setQuizFinished(false);
  };

  const goBack = () => {
    navigate("/assistant");
  };

  return (
    <div className="quiz-page">
      <h1>🧠 Quiz Time</h1>
      <p>
        Score: {score} / {quiz.length}
      </p>

      {quiz.map((q, qIndex) => (
        <div className="quiz-question" key={qIndex}>
          <p>
            <strong>
              Q{qIndex + 1}. {q.question}
            </strong>
          </p>
          <ul className="options-list">
            {q.options.map((opt, oIndex) => {
              const selected = userAnswers[qIndex] === oIndex;
              const correct = q.correctIndex === oIndex;
              let className = "";

              if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined) {
                if (selected && correct) className = "correct";
                else if (selected) className = "wrong";
                else if (correct) className = "correct";
              }

              return (
                <li
                  key={oIndex}
                  className={className}
                  onClick={() => handleAnswer(qIndex, oIndex)}
                >
                  {opt}
                </li>
              );
            })}
          </ul>

          {userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined && (
            <p className="result-msg">
              {userAnswers[qIndex] === q.correctIndex
                ? "✅ Correct!"
                : `❌ Wrong. Correct: ${q.options[q.correctIndex]}`}
            </p>
          )}
        </div>
      ))}

      <div className="quiz-actions">
        {quizFinished && <button onClick={restart}>🔁 Restart</button>}
        <button onClick={goBack}>🏠 Back to Summary</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

✅ Updated QuizPage.js with Redirect on Completion:

js
import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";
import "./QuizPage.css";

export default function QuizPage() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();
  const [quiz, setQuiz] = useState([]);
  const [userAnswers, setUserAnswers] = useState({});
  const [score, setScore] = useState(0);

  useEffect(() => {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem("quizRaw");
    if (!raw) {
      navigate("/assistant");
      return;
    }
    parseQuiz(raw);
  }, [navigate]);

  const parseQuiz = (raw) => {
    const lines = raw.split("\n").map((line) => line.trim()).filter(Boolean);

    const parsed = [];
    let currentQuestion = null;

    lines.forEach((line) => {
      if (/^\d+\./.test(line)) {
        if (currentQuestion) parsed.push(currentQuestion);
        currentQuestion = {
          question: line.replace(/^\d+\.\s*/, ""),
          options: [],
          correctIndex: null,
        };
      } else if (/^[a-dA-D]\)/.test(line)) {
        currentQuestion?.options.push(line.replace(/^[a-dA-D]\)\s*/, ""));
      } else if (/^Answer:/i.test(line)) {
        const match = line.match(/^Answer:\s*([a-dA-D])/);
        if (match) {
          currentQuestion.correctIndex = match[1].toLowerCase().charCodeAt(0) - 97;
        }
      }
    });

    if (currentQuestion) parsed.push(currentQuestion);
    setQuiz(parsed);
  };

  const handleAnswer = (qIndex, oIndex) => {
    if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined) return;

    const isCorrect = quiz[qIndex].correctIndex === oIndex;
    setUserAnswers((prev) => {
      const updated = { ...prev, [qIndex]: oIndex };

      // If last question answered, calculate score and navigate
      if (Object.keys(updated).length === quiz.length) {
        const finalScore = Object.entries(updated).reduce((acc, [i, userAns]) => {
          return acc + (quiz[i].correctIndex === userAns ? 1 : 0);
        }, 0);

        setTimeout(() => {
          navigate("/quiz-complete", {
            state: {
              score: finalScore,
              total: quiz.length,
            },
          });
        }, 1000); // Optional delay for user feedback
      }

      return updated;
    });

    if (isCorrect) setScore((prev) => prev + 1);
  };

  return (
    <div className="quiz-page">
      <h1>🧠 Quiz Time</h1>
      <p>Score: {score} / {quiz.length}</p>

      {quiz.map((q, qIndex) => (
        <div className="quiz-question" key={qIndex}>
          <p><strong>Q{qIndex + 1}. {q.question}</strong></p>
          <ul className="options-list">
            {q.options.map((opt, oIndex) => {
              const selected = userAnswers[qIndex] === oIndex;
              const correct = q.correctIndex === oIndex;
              let className = "";

              if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined) {
                if (selected && correct) className = "correct";
                else if (selected) className = "wrong";
                else if (correct) className = "correct";
              }

              return (
                <li
                  key={oIndex}
                  className={className}
                  onClick={() => handleAnswer(qIndex, oIndex)}
                >
                  {opt}
                </li>
              );
            })}
          </ul>

          {userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined && (
            <p className="result-msg">
              {userAnswers[qIndex] === q.correctIndex
                ? "✅ Correct!"
                : `❌ Wrong. Correct: ${q.options[q.correctIndex]}`}
            </p>
          )}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

Bro sometimes my quiz isnt fully generated why?
ChatGPT said:

Great question — when your quiz isn’t fully generated (e.g. fewer questions than expected), it’s usually due to one or more of these common causes related to how you're parsing or storing the quiz data:

🔍 Common Reasons Why Quiz Isn’t Fully Generated:

1. Bad formatting in the raw quiz string

If your quiz looks like this:

less
1. Question one
a) Option A
b) Option B
Answer: a

2. Question two
a) Option A
b) Option B

But "Answer: b" is missing, then question 2 won’t be considered “complete” and may be skipped.

✅ Fix: Ensure each question has:

  • A question line starting with a number + dot.

  • At least 2-4 options (a) to d)).

  • A valid answer line (like Answer: b).

2. Double newlines or hidden whitespace

If the string stored in localStorage has extra \n\n or invisible whitespace characters, it could break parsing.

✅ Fix: Before parsing, you already do this (good!):

js
const lines = raw.split("\n").map((line) => line.trim()).filter(Boolean);

Still, you might consider logging the raw value for debugging.

js
console.log("RAW INPUT:\n", raw);

3. Missing Answer: lines or unmatched option formats

In your parser, only questions with all 3 components (question, options, answer) are included:

js
if (currentQuestion) parsed.push(currentQuestion);

But it doesn’t check if the question is fully valid. If a question is partially filled (missing options or answer), it will still be pushed.

✅ Fix suggestion: Add validation before parsed.push(...):

js
if (
  currentQuestion &&
  currentQuestion.options.length >= 2 &&
  currentQuestion.correctIndex !== null
) {
  parsed.push(currentQuestion);
}

4. Stale or broken quizRaw in localStorage

If localStorage.setItem("quizRaw", ...) in your assistant page stores an incomplete or cut-off string, you’ll get a partial quiz.

✅ Fix:

  • Log it right before setting:

    js
    console.log("Generated Quiz:\n", finalQuizString);

  • Clear it before setting new data:

    js
    localStorage.removeItem("quizRaw");
localStorage.setItem("quizRaw", finalQuizString);

✅ Best Practices Going Forward:

  1. Validate the quiz string generation logic in the assistant/summarizer page.

  2. Sanitize input from OpenAI or whatever model generates the quiz.

  3. Add a "Debug" tab or log viewer for dev-only use to inspect raw quiz content.

If you're using OpenAI (like GPT) to generate the quiz, this often happens when:

  • The prompt leads to a long response

  • The token limit is nearly hit

  • The model stops early or doesn't finish due to format confusion

Fix it by:

  1. Adding "Finish the quiz completely" instruction in prompt, e.g.:

    “Generate exactly 7 multiple-choice questions from the notes, each with four options (a-d) and an answer line. Do not stop until all 7 are complete.”

  2. Using a max_tokens value that’s large enough (if using API directly).

  3. Post-process to detect and reject incomplete output, e.g. in your backend:

js
if (!quiz.includes("Answer:")) {
  return res.status(500).json({ error: "Incomplete quiz generated" });
}

🛠 Optional: Show user a fallback

If the quiz is incomplete, you could even alert the user like:

⚠️ “The quiz was not fully generated. Please try again or reduce input length.”

jsx
import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";
import "./QuizPage.css";

export default function QuizPage() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();
  const [quiz, setQuiz] = useState([]);
  const [userAnswers, setUserAnswers] = useState({});
  const [score, setScore] = useState(0);

  useEffect(() => {
    const raw = localStorage.getItem("quizRaw");
    if (!raw) {
      navigate("/assistant");
      return;
    }
    parseQuiz(raw);
  }, [navigate]);

  const parseQuiz = (raw) => {
    const lines = raw.split("\n").map(line => line.trim()).filter(Boolean);
    const parsed = [];
    let currentQuestion = null;

    lines.forEach(line => {
      if (/^\d+\./.test(line)) {
        // Push the last question if valid
        if (
          currentQuestion &&
          currentQuestion.question &&
          currentQuestion.options.length >= 2 &&
          currentQuestion.correctIndex !== null
        ) {
          parsed.push(currentQuestion);
        }
        currentQuestion = {
          question: line.replace(/^\d+\.\s*/, ""),
          options: [],
          correctIndex: null,
        };
      } else if (/^[a-dA-D]\)/.test(line)) {
        currentQuestion?.options.push(line.replace(/^[a-dA-D]\)\s*/, ""));
      } else if (/^Answer:/i.test(line)) {
        const match = line.match(/^Answer:\s*([a-dA-D])/);
        if (match) {
          currentQuestion.correctIndex = match[1].toLowerCase().charCodeAt(0) - 97;
        }
      }
    });

    // Push the final question if it's valid
    if (
      currentQuestion &&
      currentQuestion.question &&
      currentQuestion.options.length >= 2 &&
      currentQuestion.correctIndex !== null
    ) {
      parsed.push(currentQuestion);
    }

    setQuiz(parsed);
  };

  const handleAnswer = (qIndex, oIndex) => {
    if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined) return;

    const isCorrect = quiz[qIndex].correctIndex === oIndex;
    const updatedAnswers = { ...userAnswers, [qIndex]: oIndex };
    setUserAnswers(updatedAnswers);

    if (isCorrect) {
      setScore((prev) => prev + 1);
    }

    // Check if quiz is complete
    if (Object.keys(updatedAnswers).length === quiz.length) {
      const finalScore = Object.entries(updatedAnswers).reduce((acc, [i, answer]) => {
        return acc + (quiz[i].correctIndex === answer ? 1 : 0);
      }, 0);

      // Navigate after slight delay
      setTimeout(() => {
        navigate("/quiz-complete", {
          state: {
            score: finalScore,
            total: quiz.length,
          },
        });
      }, 1000);
    }
  };

  return (
    <div className="quiz-page">
      <h1>🧠 Quiz Time</h1>
      <p>Score: {score} / {quiz.length}</p>

      {quiz.map((q, qIndex) => (
        <div className="quiz-question" key={qIndex}>
          <p><strong>Q{qIndex + 1}. {q.question}</strong></p>
          <ul className="options-list">
            {q.options.map((opt, oIndex) => {
              const selected = userAnswers[qIndex] === oIndex;
              const correct = q.correctIndex === oIndex;
              let className = "";

              if (userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined) {
                if (selected && correct) className = "correct";
                else if (selected) className = "wrong";
                else if (correct) className = "correct";
              }

              return (
                <li
                  key={oIndex}
                  className={className}
                  onClick={() => handleAnswer(qIndex, oIndex)}
                >
                  {opt}
                </li>
              );
            })}
          </ul>

          {userAnswers[qIndex] !== undefined && (
            <p className="result-msg">
              {userAnswers[qIndex] === q.correctIndex
                ? "✅ Correct!"
                : `❌ Wrong. Correct: ${q.options[q.correctIndex]}`}
            </p>
          )}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

          </p>

How it stores the quiz in local storage? and what do you mean by local storage >>

Let me explain what localStorage is, and how your app is using it to store and retrieve the quiz.

🗂️ What is localStorage?

localStorage is a built-in web browser storage system that:

  • Stores small pieces of data (as key-value pairs).

  • Data is stored locally on the user's browser.

  • Persists even if the page is reloaded or the browser is closed and reopened.

  • Has a size limit (~5–10MB).

Think of it as a little notepad in the user's browser where your app can write and read temporary info.

✅ Example of How You’re Using localStorage

1. When the quiz is generated (from assistant)

Let’s say you have AI-generated quiz content like this:

less
1. What is React?
a) A CSS framework
b) A JavaScript library
c) A database
d) A programming language
Answer: b

You store it in localStorage like this:

js
localStorage.setItem("quizRaw", quizString);

  • "quizRaw" is the key.

  • quizString is the entire quiz content (raw text format).

  • This data now sits in the browser’s local memory.

2. When the Quiz Page loads

In your QuizPage.js, you retrieve that stored data:

js
const raw = localStorage.getItem("quizRaw");

Then, you parse that raw text into:

  • Questions

  • Options

  • Correct answer index

So the quiz logic and UI can be built from it dynamically.

🧠 Why Use localStorage Here?

Because it’s a temporary way to transfer data between pages without needing:

  • A backend server

  • A global state manager (like Redux)

  • URL parameters

✅ It's easy
✅ It's persistent
✅ Perfect for single-session quizzes

❗ Example Key-Value in localStorage

KeyValue (simplified)
"quizRaw""1. What is AI?\na) ...\nb) ...\nAnswer: c"

You can check this in your browser:

🧪 View in DevTools

  1. Open Chrome or Edge DevTools (F12)

  2. Go to Application tab → Local Storage

  3. Click your site under “Local Storage”

  4. You'll see keys like quizRaw

🧼 Want to Clear it?

You can remove it:

js

Or clear all:

Why use itStore quiz data between pages (like from assistant to quiz page)
How it worksYou setItem (save it) → later you getItem (read it)
